<TITLE> Rangamati District Council takes over nurses training institute </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 12 (bdnews24.com)The Rangamati Nurses Training Institute was handed over on Tuesday to the Rangamati District Council in line with the CHT peace agreement. The handover was completed in a simple ceremony at the conference room of the CHT affairs ministry at the Secretariat. As many as 20 out of the 24 institutions have now been handed over to the district council since 1998 when the deal was sealed to end decades-old bush war. The remaining four will be handed over gradually, said state minister for CHT affairs Dipankar Talukdar. The joint secretary, hospital and nursing, Abdul Jalil of the healthy ministry handed over the institute to Rangamati District Council chairman ,Jagat Jyoti Chakma in presence of Talukdar, The CHT Regional Council was formed with the leader of indigenous people, Jyotirindra Bodhipriya Larma, better known as Shantu Larma, as the founding chairman. b
